juniIgmpMIB.name: juniIgmpMIB

revisions.description: Added juniIgmpIfLocationType for support on REX platform and deprecated juniIgmpGroupsTable.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Added support for interface addresses and multicast group limits.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniIgmpMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniIgmpMIB.description: The IGMP MIB for Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniIgmpProxyGroupState.name: JuniIgmpProxyGroupState
JuniIgmpProxyGroupState.description: IP multicast group state in respect to the host IGMP (IGMP proxy) behavior.

juniIgmpGroupsTable.name: juniIgmpGroupsTable
juniIgmpGroupsTable.description: Deprecated table of max multicast groups for each physical port. This has been replaced by juniIgmpGroupsTable2.

juniIgmpGroupsEntry.name: juniIgmpGroupsEntry
juniIgmpGroupsEntry.description: Deprecated entry representing per physical port max multicast groups configurations. This has been replaced by juniIgmpGroupsEntry2.

juniIgmpGroupsSlot.name: juniIgmpGroupsSlot
juniIgmpGroupsSlot.description: Deprecated physical slot position to configure the max multicast groups for any selected port. This has been replaced by juniIgmpIfLocationIndex.

juniIgmpGroupsPort.name: juniIgmpGroupsPort
juniIgmpGroupsPort.description: Deprecated physical port to configure max multicast groups. This has been replaced by juniIgmpIfLocationIndex.

juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups.name: juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups
juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups.description: Deprecated max multicast groups limit value for each physical port. This has been replaced by juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups2.

juniIgmpIfLocationType.name: juniIgmpIfLocationType
juniIgmpIfLocationType.description: Describes the interpretation of JuniInterfaceLocationValue object values into platform-dependent interface location components, e.g., 'slot.port' on an ERX.

juniIgmpGroupsTable2.name: juniIgmpGroupsTable2
juniIgmpGroupsTable2.description: The table of max multicast groups for each physical port.

juniIgmpGroupsEntry2.name: juniIgmpGroupsEntry2
juniIgmpGroupsEntry2.description: Each entry represents per physical port max multicast groups configurations.

juniIgmpIfLocationIndex.name: juniIgmpIfLocationIndex
juniIgmpIfLocationIndex.description: The value of a platform interface location.

juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups2.name: juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups2
juniIgmpGroupsMaxGroups2.description: Configure the max multicast groups limit for each physical port.

juniIgmpInterfaceTable.name: juniIgmpInterfaceTable
juniIgmpInterfaceTable.description: The table listing the interfaces on which IGMP is enabled.

juniIgmpInterfaceEntry.name: juniIgmpInterfaceEntry
juniIgmpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry representing an interface on which IGMP is enabled.

juniIgmpInterfaceIfIndex.name: juniIgmpInterfaceIfIndex
juniIgmpInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which IGMP is enabled.

juniIgmpInterfaceQuerierTimeout.name: juniIgmpInterfaceQuerierTimeout
juniIgmpInterfaceQuerierTimeout.description: Configure other-querier-present timeout on an interface.

juniIgmpInterfaceImmediateLeave.name: juniIgmpInterfaceImmediateLeave
juniIgmpInterfaceImmediateLeave.description: Enable/disable feature to stop traffic immediately after receive leave.

juniIgmpInterfaceIoaPacketReplIfIndex.name: juniIgmpInterfaceIoaPacketReplIfIndex
juniIgmpInterfaceIoaPacketReplIfIndex.description: Configure the IOA packet replication interface.

juniIgmpRouterPromiscuous.name: juniIgmpRouterPromiscuous
juniIgmpRouterPromiscuous.description: Configure the promiscuous state of the router.

juniIgmpAdminState.name: juniIgmpAdminState
juniIgmpAdminState.description: Adminstratively enable/disable the IGMP on the router.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceTable.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceTable
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceTable.description: The IGMP proxy interface table consists of interface on which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceIfIndex.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceIfIndex
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceAddress.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceAddress
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceAddress.description: The IP address of the interface for which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceMask.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceMask
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceMask.description: The IP subnet mask of the interface for which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceState.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceState
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceState.description: When the IGMP proxy interface has v1 router present timeout running, it is in IgmpIntfStateV1RtPresent state. Otherwise, it is in IgmpIntfStateNonV1RtPresent states. While it is in IgmpIntfStateV1RtPresent, it only sends out version 1 group membership report(s). While it is in IgmpIntfStateNonV1RtPresent state, it sends out version 2 group membership report(s).

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceStatus.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceStatus
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceStatus.description: The state of the IGMP proxy interface. This object follows the RowStatus behavior. The destruction of the the row deletes the IGMP proxy inteface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceVersion.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceVersion
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceVersion.description: The version of IGMP that this IGMP proxy interface is running.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1RoutePresentTime.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1RoutePresentTimeout
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1RoutePresentTime.description: The IGMP version 1 router present timeout is the time between IGMP proxy receives a version 1 query and the time it assumes that there is no more IGMP version 1 router IGMP running. While before the V1 router present timeout expires, the IGMP proxy only sends out version 1 group membership report. When it expires, it sends out version 2 group membership report.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceUnsolicitedReportI.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceUnsolicitedReportInterval
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceUnsolicitedReportI.description: The unsolicited report interval specifies the time between the two initial group membership reports that the IGMP proxy sends.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceTotalGroupCount.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceTotalGroupCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceTotalGroupCount.description: Total number of multicast groups for this upstream interface (interface running IGMP proxy).

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceWrongVersionCount.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceWrongVersionCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceWrongVersionCount.description: Total number of wrong version of IGMP packets received on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1QueryReceiveCoun.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1QueryReceiveCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1QueryReceiveCoun.description: Total number of version 1 IGMP queries received on this interface

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2QueryReceiveCoun.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2QueryReceiveCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2QueryReceiveCoun.description: Total number of version 2 IGMP queries received on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1ReportReceiveCou.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1ReportReceiveCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1ReportReceiveCou.description: Total number of version 1 group membership reports received on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2ReportReceiveCou.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2ReportReceiveCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2ReportReceiveCou.description: Total number of version 2 group membership reports received on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1JoinReportCount.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1JoinReportCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV1JoinReportCount.description: Total number of version 1 group membership reports sent on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2JoinReportCount.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2JoinReportCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceV2JoinReportCount.description: Total number of version 2 group membership reports sent on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceLeaveReportCount.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceLeaveReportCount
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceLeaveReportCount.description: Total number of group leave reports sent on this interface.

juniIgmpProxyCacheTable.name: juniIgmpProxyCacheTable
juniIgmpProxyCacheTable.description: The IP multicast group table. The table is a union of multicast member groups from all its downstream interfaces and for which the IGMP proxy send group membership report.

juniIgmpProxyIfIndex.name: juniIgmpProxyIfIndex
juniIgmpProxyIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which IGMP proxy is enabled.

juniIgmpProxyAddress.name: juniIgmpProxyAddress
juniIgmpProxyAddress.description: The IP multicast group address that the IGMP proxy sends group membership for.

juniIgmpProxyStatus.name: juniIgmpProxyStatus
juniIgmpProxyStatus.description: The state of this entry. When the IGMP proxy has a delay time running for this multicast group, the state of this enry is in the juniIgmpDelayingMember state. When the delay time expires, the IGMP proxy sends an unsolicited report and the state of this group enters juniIgmpDelayMember state.

juniIgmpCompliance.name: juniIgmpCompliance
juniIgmpCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities that implement the Juniper IGMP MIB. This statement became obsolete when support was added for interface addresses and multicast group limits.

juniIgmpCompliance2.name: juniIgmpCompliance2
juniIgmpCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities that implement the Juniper IGMP MIB. This statement became obsolete when support was added for the administrative state object.

juniIgmpCompliance3.name: juniIgmpCompliance3
juniIgmpCompliance3.description: Deprecated compliance statement for entities that implement the Juniper IGMP MIB. This statement was deprecated when support was added for the juniIgmpIfLocationType object.

juniIgmpCompliance4.name: juniIgmpCompliance4
juniIgmpCompliance4.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement the Juniper IGMP MIB.

juniIgmpProxyInterfaceGroup.name: juniIgmpProxyInterfaceGroup
juniIgmpProxyInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of IGMP proxy interfaces in a Juniper product.

juniIgmpProxyCacheGroup.name: juniIgmpProxyCacheGroup
juniIgmpProxyCacheGroup.description: An object providing management of IGMP proxy caches in a Juniper product.

juniIgmpInterfaceGroup.name: juniIgmpInterfaceGroup
juniIgmpInterfaceGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of IGMP interfaces in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when the administrative state object was added.

juniIgmpGroupsGroup.name: juniIgmpGroupsGroup
juniIgmpGroupsGroup.description: Deprecated object providing management of IGMP global mCast groups in a Juniper product. This group was deprecated when support was added for juniIgmpIfLocationType.

juniIgmpInterfaceGroup2.name: juniIgmpInterfaceGroup2
juniIgmpInterfaceGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of IGMP interfaces in a Juniper product.

juniIgmpGroupsGroup2.name: juniIgmpGroupsGroup2
juniIgmpGroupsGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of IGMP global mCast groups in a Juniper product.
